The paper deals with weakly supervised segment annotation, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves a voting scheme that utilizes similarity measures, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper also mentions the use of kernel density estimation, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR).
